XXVII. 1 n.—promulside: the cena proper in Cicero's day was preceded by the gustus, gusta- tio, or promulsis, as it was some- times called from the mulsum or mead which was commonly drunk with this course. The promulsis consisted of light articles of food‚ such as eggs, sausage, salacis, olives, artichokes, asparagus, etc.
